    <rdfs:comment>one entity includes or holds another entity within it.</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Ne1e7560d10b04f7bb5b8cf890878caaa">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/iterable"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/ACCESS"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/iterator"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>obtaining</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the second way you can iterate the elements of a java iterable is by obtaining a java iterator from it by calling the iterable iterator() method.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N3b38638b2363446db611edc41e3bb3d5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/finer%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/EQUIVALENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/warning"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>corresponds to</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>for instance finest() finer() fine() info() warning() and severe() each corresponds to one of the log levels</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N292d5e10a3da46c2af64f26f0e2497a7">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notifyall%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/COLLABORATION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/enqueue"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>called from</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>notice how notifyall() is only called from enqueue() and dequeue() if the queue size is equal to the size bounds (0 or limit)</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N5b2f08d714b54f0ab9ac51c03b265f50">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/wait%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/COLLABORATION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notify"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>call</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>this allows other threads to call wait() or notify() too, since these methods must be called from inside a synchronized block.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N69a28bee385e432ea553a58a5c55d271">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/computeifabsent"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/DIFFERENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/compute"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>works similarly to</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the map computeifabsent() method works similarly to the compute() method but the lambda expression is only called if no entry exists already for the given key</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/connect%28%29">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/class/Method"/>
    <rdfs:label>connect()</rdfs:label>
    <prop:entityType>Method</prop:entityType>
    <prop:COLLABORATION rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/read"/>
    <prop:COLLABORATION rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/write"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N52a2735afcee4a5daeacf92ef767d52e">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notify%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/DIFFERENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notifyall"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>is considered different to</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>for inexplicable reasons it is possible for threads to wake up even if notify() and notifyall() has not been called.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N492eb65472f349b59566655acb0ee2ff">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/matcher.find"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/EXECUTION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/appendreplacement"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>called inside</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>notice how appendreplacement() is called inside the while(matcher.find()) loop, and appendtail() is called just after the loop.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/class/Interface">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label>Interface</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>an interface is a reference type in java, used to specify methods that must be implemented by a class, and can be functional or annotation-based.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N41c2fbd4178e4194928875ec81331994">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/sortedset"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/ACCESS"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/comparator"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>obtain via</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>if you created your sortedset with a comparator, you can obtain that comparator via the sortedset comparator() method.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Ndf9a1291e4fd47a0b53b063a6ccef01f">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/getconnectiontx%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/EXECUTION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/connection.setautocommit%28false"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>calls</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>inside the daocommand.execute() method the getpersondaotx() will be called, and then getconnectiontx() will be called, and then connection.setautocommit(false) will be called at that time.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Nfbe36e833c1942baa80faf5d1f141e89">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/clear%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/PREFERENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/compact"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>preference</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>you can do so either by calling clear() or by calling compact().</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/addandget%28%29">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/class/Method"/>
    <rdfs:label>addandget()</rdfs:label>
    <prop:entityType>Method</prop:entityType>
    <prop:DIFFERENCE rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/getandadd"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/schedule">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/class/Method"/>
    <rdfs:label>schedule</rdfs:label>
    <prop:entityType>Method</prop:entityType>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/property/LIMITATION">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>LIMITATION</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>one entity imposes restrictions or constraints on another entity.</rdfs:comment>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N490e8d5d128d4f06a87a4d1f28598a21">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/wait%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/COLLABORATION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notifyall"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>holding the lock</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>a thread cannot call wait() notify() or notifyall() without holding the lock on the object the method is called on</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N927fab3bebcc4955b95264a8e75a0cb4">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/method2%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/EXECUTION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/method1"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>called</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>though the error may seem the same to method1() no matter which of method2() and method3() that called it, this may important to know for the developer investigating the error.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Naf68fbc9ed3743fea9853ec952a4b461">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/sortedmap"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/ACCESS"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/comparator"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>obtaining</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>here is an example of obtaining the comparator used by a sortedmap via its comparator() method:</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N83e27e7f245246368a520063b673dbe5">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/exiting%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/EXECUTION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/entering"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>called at the end</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>for instance ordinary debug trace logging calls to entering() and exiting() would be called at the beginning and end of a method call</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/stepbefore">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
