    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/ACCESS"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/iterator"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>calling</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the second way you can iterate the elements of a java iterable is by obtaining a java iterator from it by calling the iterable iterator() method.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/finer%28%29">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/class/Method"/>
    <rdfs:label>finer()</rdfs:label>
    <prop:entityType>Method</prop:entityType>
    <prop:EQUIVALENCE rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/fine"/>
    <prop:EQUIVALENCE rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/info"/>
    <prop:EQUIVALENCE rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/warning"/>
    <prop:EQUIVALENCE rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/severe"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Nf94f5c8d38754c75a5ddc58706903ff6">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/wait%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/COLLABORATION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/lock"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>call in</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>executing unlock() sets islocked back to false, and notifies (awakens) one of the threads waiting in the wait() call in the lock() method, if any.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Ncf3a1d62e8b44d28ada51b292ea641fe">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/selector.wakeup%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/COLLABORATION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/select"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>call</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>this is done by having a different thread call the selector.wakeup() method on the selector which the first thread has called select() on.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N37a4ee751a134251adfd562453eab427">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/stop%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/LIMITATION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/lambda%20expression%29"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>no longer create</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>a stop() or pause() method too), then you can no longer create your runnable implementation with a java lambda expression.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N6ca6484c7e8e4caabf8e53f74bc8aa27">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/ceilingentry%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/DIFFERENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/ceilingkey"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>similar to</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the ceilingentry() is thus similar to the ceilingkey() method except the ceilingkey() method only returns the key and ceilingkey() returns a map.entry object containing both the key and value</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N09651798aeb4471796730a211ae3dc2b">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/getandadd%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/DIFFERENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/addandget"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>returns the value the atomicinteger had before the value was added</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the first method, addandget() adds a number to the atomicinteger and returns its value after the addition. the second method, getandadd() also adds a number to the atomicinteger but returns the value the atomicinteger had before the value was added.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N3f33b98b0d0a4b3684050bd5d91bc173">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/callsum"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/EXECUTION"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/add"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>creates</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>notice how the method callsum() creates a variable called thesum, and assigns it the value returned by the add(1, 3) method call.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/allocate%28%29">
