    <prop:relationInstance>calls</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>notice how printboth() calls the print() method two times, each time with a different of the parameters passed to the printboth() method.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N9eb8eed44f0c4098a89973e8f7f137cb">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/navigableset"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/CONTAINMENT"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/sortedset"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>includes</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the descendingiterator() method allows you to iterate the elements of the navigableset (which is also a sortedset) in reverse order, without changing the order of the elements internally.</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
