    <prop:relationInstance>named</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>these methods are named readfloat32() and readfloat64() here are two examples of reading a rion float field into a java float and double variable:</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/java-kg/class/Method">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label>Method</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>a method is a function associated with a class or interface, which can be static, instance-based, concrete, abstract, or specific to interfaces and concrete classes.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="Na4d8ccafe0864361a3df497ed8181474">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
    <rdf:subject rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notify%28%29"/>
    <rdf:predicate rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/property/DIFFERENCE"/>
    <rdf:object rdf:resource="http://example.org/java-kg/individual/notifyall"/>
    <prop:relationInstance>difference</prop:relationInstance>
    <prop:sourceText>the problem is, that since the donotify() call only calls notify() and not notifyall(), only one thread is awakened even if 4 threads are waiting on the same string instance (the empty string).</prop:sourceText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="N313ed72dd07741ad8dcf4e6c0da2eff7">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement"/>
